Rollo Lloyd https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rollo_Lloyd 0 Rollo Lloyd (March 22, 1883 – July 24, 1938) was an American actor. He appeared in the films Prestige, Okay, America!, Flaming Gold, Laughter in Hell, Today We Live, Strictly Personal, Destination Unknown, Out All Night, Madame Spy, Private Scandal, Whom the Gods Destroy, The Party's Over, The Man Who Reclaimed His Head, The Lives of a Bengal Lancer, Mad Love, Hot Tip, His Night Out, Barbary Coast, Professional Soldier, Magnificent Obsession, Hell-Ship Morgan, The Devil-Doll, Anthony Adverse, Straight from the Shoulder, Yellowstone, The Man I Marry, Love Letters of a Star, The Accusing Finger, Four Days' Wonder, Seventh Heaven, Armored Car, The Last Train from Madrid, Souls at Sea, The Women Men Marry, The Westland Case, Night Spot, Arsène Lupin Returns, Goodbye Broadway, Crime Ring and Smashing the Rackets, among others.
